@DATABASE "Default"
@NODE "Main" "Non Volatile Editor"
@TOC "MAIN"

			 @{b}Non Volatile Memory Editor@{ub}
			 --------------------------


			@{"        Introduction        " LINK Intro}

			@{"        Main screen         " LINK MainScreen}

			@{"        Menu's              " LINK "Menu"}

			@{"        Disclaimer          " LINK "Disclaimer"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Menu" "Menu"
@TOC "MAIN"
			@{b}The Pull Down Menu's@{ub}
			--------------------


			     @{" Un/Hide " link "UnHide"}

			     @{"  About  " link "About"} 

			     @{"  Quit   " link "Quit"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "UnHide" "Un/Hide"
@TOC "MAIN"

This is used to Un/Hide Window so when in hide mode Only Title bar is show.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "About" "About"
@TOC "MAIN"

Here you will find the Authors details.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Quit" "Quit"
@TOC "MAIN"

This is to exit the NV program.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "MainScreen" "MainScreen"
@TOC "MAIN"
   @{"Game Name" LINK "Game Name"}        			@{"Item Name" LINK "Item Name"}       	@{"Units" LINK "Units"}
			Text		Hex
     @{"Delete" link "Delete"}      +--------------------------------------------------------+
		  +000  .............. $00000000000000000000000000000000000+
		  +010  .............. $00000000000000000000000000000000000+
  @{"Read" link "Read"}   @{"Store" link "Store"}  +020  .............. $00000000000000000000000000000000000+
                  +030  .............. $00000000000000000000000000000000000+
		  +040  .............. $00000000000000000000000000000000000+
  @{"Lock" link "Lock"}   @{"Unlock" link "Unlock"} +050  .............. $00000000000000000000000000000000000+
		  +060  .............. $00000000000000000000000000000000000+
     @{"Info" link "Info"}        +070  .............. $00000000000000000000000000000000000+
                  +080  .............. $00000000000000000000000000000000000+
		  +090  .............. $00000000000000000000000000000000000+
		  +0A0  .............. $00000000000000000000000000000000000+
		  +0B0  .............. $00000000000000000000000000000000000+
@{"Load Item File" link "Load Item File"}   +0C0  .............. $00000000000000000000000000000000000+
		  +0D0  .............. $00000000000000000000000000000000000+
@{"Save Item File" link "Save Item File"}   +0E0  .............. $00000000000000000000000000000000000+
		  +0F0  .............. $00000000000000000000000000000000000+
		  +--------------------------------------------------------+
 @{"Status" link "Status"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Game Name" "Game Name"
@TOC "MAIN"
This is the Name of saved Non Volatile Memory game ect.  
	(Non Volatile Memory equivilent of Directory)

To enter a new Game Name click on Gadget and type in new Game Name you wish
to edit.


If you dont no what the Game Name is stored as,

You can find it out by switching the Disable switch on the back panel of
your SX-1 and from the Cd32 Logo screen press the red JoyPad button to
see the gamelock screen.  (without any Cd in your Cd32)

The Game Name is 1st Followed by "-"  Examples:


Game Name		Use Game Name
---------		-------------
Exile-1			Exile
Trolls-level		Trolls
Mcosm-Core		Mcosm
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Item Name" "Item Name"
@TOC "MAIN"

This is the Item name you are currently editing in the
Non Volatile Memory.  (Non Volatile Memory equivilent of File Name)

To enter a new Item Name click on Gadget and type in new Item Name you wish
to edit, You will only need to do this when you wish to save a new Item name.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Units" "Units"
@TOC "MAIN"

This shows the number of units used by the game loaded from Non Volatile Memory.

Each 10 bytes takes up one Unit of Non Volatile memory,  Cd32 has 100 Units.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Delete" "Delete"
@TOC "MAIN"

This Delete's Items in the Non Volatile Memory, that you don't
want any more.						@{"Selector" LINK "Selector"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Read" "Read"
@TOC "MAIN"

This Read's Non Volatile Memory into a buffer so you can
edit them, or save to disk ect.		   		@{"Selector" LINK "Selector"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Store" "Store"
@TOC "MAIN"

This will save the buffer to the Non Volatile Memory.	@{"Selector" LINK "Selector"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Lock" "Lock"
@TOC "MAIN"

This will Lock a Item name in Non Volatile Memory.	@{"Selector" LINK "Selector"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Unlock" "Unlock"
@TOC "MAIN"

This will Unlock a Item name in Non Volatile Memory.	@{"Selector" LINK "Selector"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Selector"
@TOC "MAIN"

A Item Name selector will be displayed, which you use to select the Item name
you wish to use.

Note:	If you wish to save a new Item Name Enter the Name in the Item Name
	Gadget and click on Ok.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Info" "Info"
@TOC "MAIN"

This will tell you how much space is left on the Non Volatile Memory.

Max Units	- Max Available Units of Non Volatile Memory  (100 on CD32)

Free Units 	- Available Free Non Volatile Memory Units

?		- Not used yet 
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Load Item File" "Load Item File"
@TOC "MAIN"

Load a file you saved from Disk/Harddrive.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Save Item File" "Save Item File"
@TOC "MAIN"

Save a file you edited or downloaded from the Non Volatile Memory to Disk.

The size of the file saved is 10 x the Units size.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Status" "Status"
@TOC "MAIN"

Show's you the current status of operations of nv program.
@ENDNODE

